Not answering because don't know for sure:

I believe only EECS and LSCS seniors get priority for 16a. 

Try schedule.berkeley.edu for wait lists. It has enrollment and wait list data.

The categories that had reserved seats are listed @1192.

That said, I believe all of these categories are full.

I don't know if there is any priority for getting off the waitlist.

The number of open seats can be found both on schedule.berkeley.edu as well as in the schedule planner.

history.content: The priority categories are full except for the students who received permission numbers. These students were mostly CS Scholars and seniors. These students have until next week to use the permission numbers. Unfortunately, the enrollment count does not communicate with the permission number system so it appears that more seats are available than there actually are. In about a week, we will know more about how many seats there are left and who they are going to.

I am currently in position 95 on the ee16a waitlist, according to CalCentral. I'm not sure how to check the current enrollment status as the new system apparently does not display when certain seats are filled. I'm a declared LSCS major, does anybody know where that ranks for priority for ee16a? Also, where can I check the number of open seats left to be filled from the waitlist?
